data.title: Kennesaw State University Athletics
data.text:
Football 10/23/2015 10:00:00 AM By Al Barba

FB: Kennesaw State-Liberty Game to air on WUPA-TV Atlanta's CW69

Kickoff Slated for 7 p.m.

CW69 | ESPN3 | Listen Live | Game Notes

KENNESAW, Ga. â€“ For the second time this season, the Kennesaw State football team will appear on television throughout the greater Atlanta area when WUPA-TV (Atlanta's CW69) will air Saturday's game at Liberty in Lynchburg, Va. Kickoff is scheduled for 7 p.m. (ET).

WUPA-TV can be found on 810 on Comcast, 1069 on U-Verse, 709 on Charter, 69 on DirecTV and 6376 on DISH TV.

Kennesaw State enters the game 5-1 overall and 1-0 in the Big South Conference, while Liberty is 3-4 and 0-2 in conference play. The Flames are defending conference champions and advanced to the second round of the Football Championship Subdivision (FCS) playoffs a year ago.

The Owls made history last week when they defeated Gardner-Webb, 12-7, at Fifth Third Bank Stadium to become the first newcomer to win its Big South Conference debut.

Fans not in the greater Atlanta area can watch the game on ESPN3.com or listen to live at KSUOwls.com. Brian Giffin, Tutan Reyes and Art Eckman will describe the action.

Fifth Third Bank is the Official Bank of Kennesaw State Athletics. Fifth Third Bank Stadium is the home of women's soccer, women's lacrosse and football.

Keep up with Kennesaw State Athletics by following KSU on Twitter @KSUOwlNation and or by liking Kennesaw State Owls on Facebook. You also can follow Kennesaw State football at @KennesawSTFB and The Owls fund on Twitter at @TheOwlsFund.

#GoKSUOwls
